    "description": "Chuokeizai-Sha Holdings, Inc. engages in publishing business in Japan. The company publishes books and magazines related to law, economics, management, accounting, taxation and information, certifications and qualifications, and other social sciences. It also offers practical business books, textbooks for universities and junior colleges, and study books for various qualification exams and certifications, as well as practical books on IT. In addition, the company publishes magazines, including Corporate Accounting that aims to study and explain accounting theory and accounting standards; Tax News, which provides legal interpretations and processing guidelines; Monthly Accounting that offers news and commentary on accounting, taxation, finance, securities, and legal matters; and Business Law, which provides explanations of legal practices for companies and exam information for the business law examination hosted by the Tokyo Chamber of Commerce and Industry and local chambers of commerce. Further, it plans and produces corporate PR magazines and newsletters; and operates online store for books and magazines. The company was formerly known as Chuokeizai-Sha, Inc. and changed its name to Chuokeizai-Sha Holdings, Inc. in January 2016. Chuokeizai-Sha Holdings, Inc. was incorporated in 1948 and is headquartered in Chiyoda, Japan."
